@page "/about"

<PageTitle>About PdfToolStack — Built by a Developer Who Got Tired of Bad PDF Tools</PageTitle>
<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="PdfToolStack was built by a software developer with 7 years in healthcare IT, frustrated by overpriced, overcomplicated PDF tools. Simple, powerful, privacy-first." />
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://pdftoolstack.com/about" />
</HeadContent>

<div class="about-page">
    <div class="about-container">

        <!-- Hero -->
        <div class="about-hero">
            <div class="about-hero-text">
                <span class="about-tag">Our Story</span>
                <h1>Built by someone who got tired of bad PDF tools</h1>
                <p class="about-lead">
                    PdfToolStack started as a personal project — and grew into
                    something a lot of other people apparently needed too.
                </p>
                <div class="about-hero-image">
                    <img src="/images/blog/about-developer.svg"
                         alt="Developer working with PDF documents and AI tools"
                         style="width:100%; max-width:640px; margin-top:2rem;" />
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Founder story -->
        <div class="about-story">

            <div class="about-story-block">
                <h2>Where this came from</h2>
                <p>
                    I'm a software developer with seven years working in healthcare IT.
                    That means reports. Lots of them. PDFs with patient data, compliance
                    documents, audit trails, insurance forms — the kind of files where
                    getting something wrong actually matters.
                </p>
                <p>
                    What I kept running into was how <em>painful</em> the tooling was.
                    PDF files are deceptively complex under the hood, and most tools either
                    treat them as a solved problem (they're not) or charge enterprise prices
                    for features that should be basic. I'd bounce between four different
                    sites to do what should have been one workflow.
                </p>
                <p>
                    So I built PdfToolStack. Not as a startup play — just as something
                    I actually wanted to use.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="about-story-block">
                <h2>The thing that really frustrated me</h2>
                <p>
                    Almost every PDF tool I tried hid its best features behind a free trial.
                    You'd upload your file, get halfway through the process, and then hit a
                    wall — <em>sign up to download your result</em>. Or worse, the watermark
                    would appear after you'd already done the work.
                </p>
                <p>
                    I wanted to build something different. You can use all 35+ tools on
                    PdfToolStack without creating an account. No signup wall mid-task.
                    No watermarks on output. The free tier is genuinely free.
                </p>
                <p>
                    If you need AI tools, larger files, or batch processing — that's Pro,
                    and it's $19/month. Straightforward.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="about-story-block">
                <h2>Who I built this for</h2>
                <p>
                    Honestly? People like the ones I worked alongside for seven years.
                    Coordinators, administrators, and analysts who process 20–50 PDFs a
                    day and don't have time for software that fights them. Accountants
                    manually copying invoice data into spreadsheets. Paralegals comparing
                    contract versions by eye. HR teams printing forms just to sign them.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The AI tools — contract review, invoice extraction, document summarization
                    — exist because those are the problems I watched smart people solve slowly,
                    by hand, every single day.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="about-story-block">
                <h2>Privacy is not a feature — it's the default</h2>
                <p>
                    Healthcare taught me one thing clearly: documents contain things that
                    matter to real people. Your invoice has your vendor relationships in it.
                    Your contract has your negotiating position. Your HR files have someone's
                    livelihood.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Every file you upload to PdfToolStack is deleted within one hour.
                    We never train AI models on your documents. We never sell your data.
                    We don't run ads. This isn't marketing copy — it's just how the
                    system is built.
                </p>
            </div>

        </div>

        <!-- Stats row -->
        <div class="about-stats">
            <div class="about-stat">
                <div class="about-stat-number">35+</div>
                <div class="about-stat-label">PDF tools</div>
            </div>
            <div class="about-stat">
                <div class="about-stat-number">1 hr</div>
                <div class="about-stat-label">File deletion</div>
            </div>
            <div class="about-stat">
                <div class="about-stat-number">$0</div>
                <div class="about-stat-label">To get started</div>
            </div>
            <div class="about-stat">
                <div class="about-stat-number">7 yrs</div>
                <div class="about-stat-label">Industry experience</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Tech stack trust block -->
        <div class="about-tech">
            <h2>Built on infrastructure you can trust</h2>
            <p>
                PdfToolStack runs on Microsoft Azure (West US 2), built with
                ASP.NET Core and Blazor WebAssembly — the same stack used by
                enterprise healthcare and financial systems. AI features are
                powered by Claude (Anthropic), one of the most capable and
                safety-focused AI models available.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- CTA -->
        <div class="about-cta">
            <h2>Give it a try</h2>
            <p>No account needed. No free trial. Just upload a file and go.</p>
            <div class="about-cta-buttons">
                <a href="/" class="process-button"
                   style="text-decoration:none; display:inline-block; padding:0.75rem 2rem;">
                    Try the tools free
                </a>
                <a href="mailto:hello@pdftoolstack.com"
                   style="text-decoration:none; display:inline-flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; padding:0.75rem 2rem; border:1.5px solid #9795B5; border-radius:var(--radius-sm); font-size:0.95rem; font-weight:600; color:var(--text-secondary); background:transparent; white-space:nowrap; width:auto; font-family:inherit;">
                    Say hello
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>
</div>
